Combine first eight ingredients, mixing well; shape into 36 one-inch meatballs. Cook in oil over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned. Drain on paper towels. Combine grape jelly and chili sauce in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring until well combined, about 3 minutes. Place cooked or thawed meatballs in a single layer in skillet coating each meatball evenly with sauce. Cover; simmer 10 minutes stirring occasionally, until sauce is bubbly and meatballs are heated through. Transfer glazed meatballs to a chafing dish or slow cooker. Serve with frilly toothpicks.